      "raw": "1. Calculate Number of Risers (rounded up): $$ RiserCount = \\lceil \\frac{TotalRise}{MaxRiserHeight} \\rceil $$ 2. Calculate Actual Riser Height: $$ RiserHeight = \\frac{TotalRise}{RiserCount} $$ 3. Calculate Number of Treads: $$ TreadCount = RiserCount - 1 $$ 4. Calculate Tread Depth & Total Run (if Total Run not provided): $$ \\text{Ideal TreadDepth} \\approx 25 \\text{ inches} - (2 \\times RiserHeight) $$ $$ \\text{Actual TreadDepth} = \\max(\\text{Ideal TreadDepth}, \\text{MinTreadDepth}) $$ $$ TotalRun = TreadCount \\times \\text{Actual TreadDepth} $$ 5. Calculate Stringer Length (Pythagorean Theorem): $$ StringerLength = \\sqrt{TotalRise^2 + TotalRun^2} $$ 6. Calculate Bottom Riser Cut (Adjusted for Tread Thickness): $$ BottomRiserCut = RiserHeight - TreadThickness $$"
